  "articleSummary": "The article argues that large language models are fundamentally probabilistic pattern-matching engines rather than computational tools, making them inherently unreliable for mathematical tasks. Targeted at AI developers, it advocates for a pragmatic solution: using AI SDK tool calling to route mathematical queries to dedicated symbolic engines like CortexJS. Written as a pragmatic analysis with tutorial elements, the piece employs the recurring metaphor of asking a “gymnast to balance a checkbook” to frame the mismatch between linguistic fluency and numerical precision. It concludes with a practical implementation guide demonstrating how batch-processing tools and symbolic parsing can bridge natural language prompting with guaranteed computational accuracy.",
